						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in a field about a mile away on the boundry of the village.</p>						

						<p>Davaliyarāju.</p>						

						<p>Refers to a gift of paddy fields <hi rend="italic">(pannasa)</hi> by one Dhavaliyarāja, probably of the Mahābali family. Refers also to the coin <hi rend="italic">gadyāna</hi> and a land measure <hi rend="italic">maruturu.</hi></p>						

